I knew that Bryant's self-indulgence couldn't be hurt by a thrash-talk to discourage his sports rage.
Kobi had a killer instinct, so I tried to talk him out of the game in an aggressive way on the court.
On the platform I gave him compliments: "Oh!
Koby, scored well, a great pass!
Listening to my enthusiastic responses, he almost forgot that it is necessary to take the ball once again and score another 3 - 4 points.
We communicated well with Kobi," Kirilenko quotes Evening Moscow as saying.
He also spoke about his first game against Jordan.
"I took care of him.
The first three minutes of the match I ran in full admiration of the fact that there is a legend next to me that I saw only on TV.
While I'm having a breath of joy in the tooth, Michael scored a lot of points.
Soon I went away from delight, a couple of times covered his throws...
In that game, my team won, and Jordan still scored 44 points," added the head of the RFB.
Kirilenko spent 12 seasons in the NBA.
He was selected 24th overall by the Utah Jazz in the 1999 draft.
In addition to Utah, for which he spent ten seasons, the Russian forward played for the Minnesota Timberwolves and the Brooklyn Nets.
In a total of 797 games he averaged 11.8 points, 5.5 rebounds, 2.7 assists and 1.8 blocks.
